(983, 'EX-069644', 'MC', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt\">Having the correct attitude to work is called -------------</span></span></span></p>\r\n', 'Devotion to duty', 'Divotion of duty', 'Acceptance of duty', 'Division of labour', 'Absent from duty.', 'option1', ''),
(984, 'EX-698575', 'MC', '<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">PASSAGE I</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Read the passages below and answer the questions that follow by choosing the most appropriate of the options lettered A -E (Nos. 1-10)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">The first murder ever committed in the United States occurred in September 1630, shortly after the Pilgrims arrived in Massachusetts. John Billington was the father of two sons, one of the first to settle in the new Plymouth Colony near what is today Boston, and one of the people who signed the Mayflower Compact&mdash;and he was also the colony&rsquo;s first murderer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Billington, in fact, was the first person to commit any crime in the colony, as far as we know today. He was also the first to be executed by the state in the New World. Billington&rsquo;s crime was to shoot a man named John Newcomen, for reasons which are lost to history.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">But Billington&rsquo;s problems had not begun on the soil of North America. He and his two sons had nearly caused a mutiny aboard the Mayflower during the arduous trip across the ocean. One of his sons, in fact, fired his gun aboard the Mayflower&mdash;near an open keg of gunpowder! The flash from the gun could easily have ignited the powder, which would probably have sunk the ship.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Once in Plymouth Colony, Billington&rsquo;s behavior did not improve. He refused to serve any form of military duty under the leadership of Miles Standish, a duty that was seen by the colonists as part of every man&rsquo;s responsibilities in the New World. He was later implicated in a plot to overthrow the entire leadership of Plymouth Colony, but a lack of evidence prompted the town&rsquo;s leaders to let him go free. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">In the end, Billington&rsquo;s rebellious and angry nature caught up with him. He was found guilty of the murder of John Newcomen, and died in disgrace on the gallows.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">Based on the information in the passage, which of the following best describes John Billington?</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', 'quiet and shy', 'angry and rebellious', 'clever and amusing', 'bold and patriotic', 'scared and sorry', 'option2', '');
